      "span_text": "Glycosylated monomeric stilbene glucosides (astringin, isorhapontin, and piceid) are structurally similar to by far the most extensively studied stilbenoid, trans-resveratrol, for which there is a vast amount of accumulated scientific evidence on its multiple biological activities, including antioxidant  .",
